atered terrain around the meridian seems to be geologically\nold while the western bulge is relatively young. The latitudinal variation in\ncrater density suggests that the equatorial ridge of Ryugu is a geologically\nold structure; however, this could be alternatively explained by a collision\nwith many fission fragments during a short rotational period of Ryugu in the\npast.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 12 May 2022 00:56:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-13"}
