ge usually does not\nexceed $\\Delta N=4$ and $\\Delta Z=4$, i.e., it is rather short. This result\nsuggests that the frequently made assumption of reduced statistical errors for\nthe differences between smoothly-varying observables cannot be generally\njustified.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 12 May 2022 15:04:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-07-20"}
